    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-08-12T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-08-12T19:00:00-05:00" n="662"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d662">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48 Refugees/8–1244: Circular telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Australia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="52" xml:id="d662fn52">Repeated on the same date to Canada,
                        the Dominican Republic, El Salvador, Guatemala, Honduras, Ireland,
                        Nicaragua, Paraguay, and Peru.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-08-12T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 12, 1944—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Reference previous communications regarding refugee children. In view of the
                    situation in Hungary and the recent statement by Admiral Horthy that his
                    Government would grant exit permits to, and suspend deportations of, all Jewish
                    children for whom havens may be provided outside Hungary, would you request the
                    government to which you are accredited to extend its acceptance in principle to
                    children from Hungary as well as from France.</p>
                <p>You may assure appropriate officials of that government that no detailed plans
                    have as yet been developed for the actual immigration of refugee children into
                    its country. Should such plans become necessary at a later date, they will not
                    be developed without previous consultation with the government to which you are
                        accredited.<note n="53" xml:id="d662fn53">Governments accepting extension of
                        this principle included Ireland, the Dominican Republic, Honduras,
                        Nicaragua, and Paraguay. Ecuador agreed to accept 300 European children and
                        Brazil to receive 500 Jewish refugee children from Hungary. Offers of asylum
                        for Jewish children from Hungary were made also by Sweden and
                        Switzerland.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
